Upon further analysis, it can be observed that the compound contains one carbon atom, two fluorine atoms, and one oxygen atom. The arrangement of these atoms suggests a cyclic structure, with carbon serving as the central atom bonded to two fluorine atoms and one oxygen atom. 

Therefore, the molecular formula of C1C(C1(F)F)C(=O)O can be expressed as C2F2O, representing two carbon atoms, two fluorine atoms, and one oxygen atom in a cyclic arrangement. This molecular formula provides insight into the composition and structure of the compound, allowing for further examination of its chemical properties and behavior.
